All World: The Greatest Hits is the first greatest hits compilation from hip hop artist LL Cool J, released in 1996. It covers his career from the time of his Def Jam debut Radio, to his 1995 album Mr. Smith. One noticeable track missing is his 1989 song &quot;I'm That Type of Guy&quot; which was not added to the album list. Instead a remix of his 1995 track &quot;Loungin&quot; from Mr. Smith was added which features R&amp;B trio Total.[citation needed] All World has since been certified Platinum by the RIAA.



